===Etymology===
* First attested in the mid 15th century.
* From {{etyl|enm|en}}, '''and''' from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|accusatif|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|acusatif|lang=frm}} '''or''' from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term/t|la|accūsātīvus||of accusing}}, from {{term|accusatus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term/t|la|accūsō}}. The Latin form was mis-translated from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|αιτιατική|lang=grc}} + {{term|πτώσις|tr=ptōsis||case of that which was caused|lang=grc}} from {{term|αιτία||accusation or cause|lang=grc}}.
* See [[accuse]].

